ic: it does not ask whether models should pass, only what happens when they do (\"passes both content checks\"). No real OS/network primitive is required to expose publish-vs-hold/drop logic.","test_description":"Wire moderation service, persistence, and publisher with deterministic passing classifier fakes; submit posts and assert final state is published, with no hold record and no dropped message.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.07,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The full moderation pipeline — image check, text check, publish decision — completes within 5 seconds of submission.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"Behavior explicitly spans multiple agentic steps in sequence (image model + text model + decision), so MULTI-STEP applies. A lower-level latency test with stubs can miss real queueing/variance across chained model calls. This is not just one API boundary; it is end-to-end multi-stage moderation timing.","test_description":"Execute end-to-end submissions through real image and text moderation calls under peak-hour representative concurrency, and assert end-to-end completion time (e.g., p95) stays within 5 seconds from ingest to final decision.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.03,"System":0.17,"Agentic":0.25,"Workflow":0.55}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the AI vision model is unavailable, image posts are queued for retry rather than auto-approved.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Primary failure boundary is real dependency outage behavior (timeouts, connection failures, 5xx), which is real infra (REAL-INFRA yes). Integration fakes may hide transport-level failure modes and exception mappings. Agentic is not required because correctness does not depend on model output content, only outage handling.","test_description":"Run the service against a re